chen Tierbildern und geben damit einen Überblick über aktuelle Forschungsfragen der Human-Animal Studies.  aThis multi-faceted volume enriches the current debate on social human-animal relationships. The discussion revolves around issues of animal ethics, negotiation of the human-animal boundary, and is concerned with, if nothing else, concrete interactions.Interdisciplinary contributions take up these issues on the basis of the core themes »animal economies« and »animal images«. From different perspectives, they approach the relationship between animals and economics as well as the diverse forms and functions of social animal images, thereby offering an overview of current research issues in human-animal studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aBild. 4aKulturwissenschaft. 4aMensch-Tier-Grenze. 4aMensch. 4aTier. 4aTierbilder. 4aTiere. 4aTiergeschichte. 4aTierphilosophie. 4aÖkonomie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aAnimal History.  aAnimal Philosophy.  aCultural Studies.  aHuman Animal Studies.  aHuman.  aImage.1 aArbeitskreis, Chimaira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChimaira - Arbeitskreis für Human-Animal Studies, , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDittrich, Annett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeubach, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKruse, Ulrike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMackinger, Christof, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMönnig, Mona, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPetrus, Klaus, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosen, Aiyana, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/